# Orchestrator Skill Routing

Use these skills by default when editing the swarm orchestrator codebase.

## Core orchestration (`swarm/flow.py`, `swarm/worker.py`, `swarm/task_store.py`, `swarm/task_models.py`)

- `python-error-handling`
- `python-resilience`
- `python-observability`
- `python-performance-optimization` (when throughput or latency is part of the task)

## Tests and behavior locks (`tests/**`)

- `python-testing-patterns`

## MCP and tool contracts (`swarm/mcp_server.py`, `swarm/tools/**`)

- `mcp-builder`

## API contracts and request/response design (`swarm/api.py`)

- `api-design-principles`

## CI/CD workflow changes (`.github/workflows/**`)

- `github-actions-templates`

Prefer deterministic pipeline behavior (`BUILD -> REVIEW LOOP -> QUALITY -> POLISH`) and preserve in-memory fallback behavior when queue/worker code changes.
